SIMPLE: mortifying
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mortifying
<hw>Mor"ti*fy`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Tending to mortify; affected by, or having symptoms of,
mortification; <as>as, a <ex>mortifying</ex> wound; <ex>mortifying</ex>
flesh.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Subduing the appetites, desires, etc.; <as>as,
<ex>mortifying</ex> penances</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tending to humble or abase; humiliating; <as>as, a
<ex>mortifying</ex> repulse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortifyingly</ent>⟦br⟧
